cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI

The paper deals with game theory and its representation in extensive games. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science - Game Theory). The paper also discusses the concept of Nash equilibrium, which is a key concept in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Computer Science - Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also deals with the representation of games from the point of view of every agent, which is a topic in machine learning and decision making, making cs.LG (Computer Science - Learning) a possible category. The paper also discusses the structure of game trees, which is a topic in data structures, making cs.DS (Computer Science - Data Structures and Algorithms) another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses subjective games, which involve beliefs and knowledge, making cs.SI (Computer Science - Social and Information Networks) a possible category.
